-- China Plans Digital Publishing 25% Industry Sales by 2015, Xinhua Says
-- B y   B l o o m b e r g   N e w s
-- 2010-09-22T03:38:29Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-09-22/china-digital-publishing-to-make-25-of-total-sales-by-2015-xinhua-says.html
China plans to generate a quarter
of its publication industry’s revenue through digital publishing
by the end of 2015, Xinhua news agency reported today, citing a
government blueprint.  China’s General Administration of Press and Publication’s
blueprint says it aims to get all publishers to offer their
products digitally by 2020, according to the report.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Stanley James at 
 sjames8@bloomberg.net  